{{Infobox football biography | name = Ernst Jean-Joseph | image = Bundesarchiv Bild 183-N0615-0032, Fußball-WM, Italien - Haiti 3-1.jpg | caption = Jean-Joseph (on the ground, left) versus [[Italy national football team|Italy]] | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1948|06|11|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Cap-Haïtien]], [[Haiti]] | death_date = | height = | position = [[Midfielder]] | years1 = | clubs1 = [[Violette A.C.]]| | years2 = 1978 | clubs2 = [[Chicago Sting]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | caps2 = 9 | goals2 = 0 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]]| nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = }}
'''Ernst Jean-Joseph''' (born 11 June 1948) is a [[Haiti]]an [[association football|football]] [[midfielder]] who played for [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]] in the [[1974 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/edition=39/teams/team=43908.html 1974 FIFA World Cup Germany]</ref> He played for [[Violette A.C.]] and [[Chicago Sting]].<ref>[http://www.nasljerseys.com/Players/J/Jean-Joseph.Ernst.htm NASL career stats]</ref>
Soon after Haiti's decent showing against Italy in the tournament - a game in which Jean-Joseph's team had briefly led - celebrations were undermined by his failing of a dope test. Haiti's officials meted out their own punishment before flying the player home. <ref>http://www.sabotagetimes.com/football-sport/how-voodoo-and-gangsters-took-haiti-to-the-world-cup-part-2/</ref>
